U.S. Treasury Department Schedule for Tuesday, April 26

-- B y   V i n c e n t   D e l   G i u d i c e
-- 
2011-04-26T13:03:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/u-s-treasury-department-schedule-for-tuesday-april-26.html
The following is a reformatted
version of the U.S. Treasury Department’s daily release on the
schedule for Secretary Timothy F. Geithner and other officials:  On Tuesday morning, Secretary Geithner will be in  New York
City  to deliver remarks and participate in a question and answer
discussion at the  Council on Foreign Relations . In opening
remarks and a subsequent discussion moderated by Bloomberg L.P.
President Daniel L. Doctoroff, the Secretary will address the
path forward for fiscal policy, the debt limit, strengthening
U.S. competitiveness, and the state of the global economy. This
event is open press.  Also in the morning, Treasurer Rios will participate in an
event to “retire” paper checks for new recipients of social
security and other federal benefits. The Treasury Department’s
move to electronic payment for all federal benefits is excepted
to save more than $1 billion over the next ten years. At the
event, Treasurer Rios will highlight these savings by signing a
ceremonial check for $1 billion made out to the American
taxpayer. This event is open press.  Later, Secretary Geithner will participate in a roundtable
discussion with business leaders organized by the Partnership
for New York City. This event is closed press.  On Tuesday afternoon, Secretary Geithner will return to
 Washington , DC.  In the evening, the Secretary will attend a dinner meeting
with Crown Prince Mohammed bin Zayed  Al Nahyan  of the  United
Arab Emirates  who is in Washington for meetings with President
Obama. The dinner is closed press.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Del Giudice in Washington 
 vdelgiudice@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Wellisz at   cwellisz@bloomberg.net  